{"lemma":"آيَةٌ","slug":"آيَةٌ","root":"#.#.#","root_slug":"_-_-_","root_link":"/words/roots/_-_-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun_prop","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"آيَة","root":"أيي","pos":"N","occurrence_count":382},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["pron"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n1638","n1639","n1643"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A2%D9%8A%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"pron","gloss":"feminine of أَيّ (ʔayy)","tags":["feminine","form-of"],"examples":[{"text":"al-Kumayt ibn Zayd al-Asadi\nبِأَيِّ كِتَابٍ أَمْ بِأَيَّةِ سُنَّةٍ\nتَرَى حُبَّهُمْ عَارًا عَلَيَّ وَتَحْسَبُ\nbi-ʔayyi kitābin ʔam bi-ʔayyati sunnatin\ntarā ḥubbahum ʕāran ʕalayya wa-taḥsabū"}]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ʔaj.ja/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n1638","headword_ar":"اَيْهَ","root":"Ayh","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"text","text":"would seem to be a dial. var. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wayoha","text_ar":"وَيْهَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; for it is said that]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ayohaka","text_ar":"اَيْهَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wayohaka","text_ar":"وَيْهَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K: [but see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wayoha","text_ar":"وَيْهَ"},{"kind":"text","text":".])       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ayohFA","text_ar":"اَيْهًا"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ayohaAta","text_ar":"اَيْهَاتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n1639","headword_ar":"اـِيهْ","root":"Ayh","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", with the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h","text_ar":"ه"},{"kind":"text","text":"quiescent, is a word used in chiding, or checking; meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hasobuka","text_ar":"حَسْبُكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Sufficient for thee"},{"kind":"text","text":"is such a thing; &c.]. (ISd, K.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iyhFA","text_ar":"اـِيهًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies, (S, K,) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ayha","text_ar":"ايهَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) a command to be silent, (S, K,) and to abstain; (S, TA;) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Be silent;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abstain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"desist:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) both are used in chiding, or checking: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hiyha","text_ar":"هِيهَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used in the place of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iyha","text_ar":"اـِيهَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Lth, TA.) You say [also,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iyhFA Ean~aA","text_ar":"اـِيهًا عَنَّا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Be silent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abstain from"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"troubling"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"us."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iyhaA Ean~iY A@loA=na","text_ar":"اـِيهَا عَنِّى ا@لْا=نَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Abstain thou from"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Troubling"},{"kind":"text","text":"] me now. (AZ, TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iyhFA","text_ar":"اـِيهًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"also occurs as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I hold that to be true, and approve it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAth, TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iyhi","text_ar":"اـِيهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iyha","text_ar":"اـِيهَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iyhK","text_ar":"اـِيهٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", is a word denoting a desire, or demand, for one to add, or to give, or do, more; (Lth, K;) and a desire for one to speak: (K:) it (i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iyhi","text_ar":"اـِيهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":") is an imperative verbal noun, (S,) indecl., with kesr for its termination: (K:) you say to a man, when you desire, or demand, his telling or saying more of a [certain] story or subject of discourse, or his doing more of a [certain] deed,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iyhi","text_ar":"اـِيهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with kesr. to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h","text_ar":"ه"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;) [i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Tell me,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"say, more of this; say on; go on,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"proceed, with this;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"do more of this;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@foEalo A_iyhi","text_ar":"ا@فْعَلْ اـِيهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Go on,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"proceed, with this; do it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (AZ;) and for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iyhi","text_ar":"اـِيهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hiyhi","text_ar":"هِيهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Lth:) but when you make no interruption after it, you pronounce it with tenween, (ISk, S, K,) and say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iyhK","text_ar":"اـِيهٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (ISk, S,) which means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Had~ivonaA","text_ar":"حَدِّثْنَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Tell us,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"relate to us, something"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (Ks, Lh, (ISk, * S; *) and for this one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hiyhK","text_ar":"هِيهٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", by substitution of one letter for another: (Ks, Lh:) or it means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zido","text_ar":"زِدْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tell,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"say,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"do, something more"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"haAti","text_ar":"هَاتِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"give,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"relate, something"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (Har p. 592;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"takal~ama","text_ar":"تَكَلَّمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"speak"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Idem p. 419.) In the following saying of Dhu-r-Rummeh,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"waqafonaA wa qulonaA A_iyhi Eano A^um~i saAlimK\n                      \n                     \n                        wa maA baAlu takoliymi Ald~iyaAri AlbalaAqiEi"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"We stopped, and we said, Tell us some tidings:"},{"kind":"text","text":"inform us ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axobiriynaA","text_ar":"اَخْبِرِينَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"being app. understood)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"respecting Umm-Sálim: but what is the case"},{"kind":"text","text":"(meaning what is the use)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of speaking to the vacant dwellings?"},{"kind":"text","text":"], he has used the word without tenween, though making no interruption after it, because he intended a pause. (ISk, S.) Ibn-Es-Seree says, When you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iyhi yaA rajulu","text_ar":"اـِيهِ يَا رَجُلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", you only command him to tell you more of the subject of discourse known to you and him, as though you said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"haAti AlHadiyva","text_ar":"هَاتِ الحَدِيثَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Give,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"relate, the story,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"narrative, O man"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: but if you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iyhK","text_ar":"اـِيهٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with tenween, it is as though you said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"haAti HadiyvFA m~aA","text_ar":"هَاتِ حَدِيثًا مَّا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Give,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"relate, some story"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"narrative"},{"kind":"text","text":"], because the tenween renders indeterminate: and Dhu-rRummeh meant the tenween, but omitted it through necessity. (S.) As says that Dhu-rRummeh has committed a mistake; the expression of the Arabs being only"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iyhK","text_ar":"اـِيهٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in a case of this kind]: ISd says, the truth is, that it is without tenween when determinate, and with tenween when indeterminate; and that Dhu-r-Rummeh asks the ruins to tell him more of a known story, as though he said,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Relate to us the story,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tell us the tidings:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) Aboo-Bekr Ibn-Es-Sarráj says, citing this verse, that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ayh","text_ar":"ايه"},{"kind":"text","text":"is not known in a case of this kind without tenween in any of the dialects; meaning that it is never conjoined with a following word unless it be with tenween. (IB, TA.)"},{"kind":"page_break","n":140}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA","Lth","ISk","Ks","Lh"]},{"entry_id":"n1643","headword_ar":"اَيِّهٌ","root":"Ayh","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Having a strong,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"loud, voice; and vigilant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wary."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 675.)"}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D8%A2%D9%8A%D8%A9/","headword_ar":"آية","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_18","lexicon_en":"Al-Sharīf al-Jurjānī, Kitāb al-Taʿrīfāt (d. 1413 CE)","lexicon_ar":"كتاب التعريفات للشريف الجرجاني","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=23001#b91993","body_html":"<span>الآية: هي طائفةٌ من القرآن يتصل بعضها ببعض إلى انقطاعها، طويلةً كانت أو قصيرة. </span>"}]}}